This paper is about using deep neural networks for retinal vessel segmentation, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel method that utilizes U-net with residual connection and an edge-aware mechanism, which involves adding additional labels on boundary areas to improve accuracy. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper involves image processing and analysis, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR).
